The Evermeet underfoundation has a more serious problem than wandering shades. A remnant guardian has established itself in the east vault — a cohesive entity associated with whatever was once stored in the alcoves there. The Society's research team cannot get past it, and the warden corps does not extend jurisdiction below road level. We need someone to go into the east vault and remove it permanently. The guardian is not a wandering shade — it is purposeful, aware, and defensive of the alcove space. Reward reflects the difficulty. The site will be considerably more accessible to legitimate research afterward.
The east vault of the Evermeet underfoundation is quiet. The research team reports the guardian's manifestation has fully dispersed, and the alcove area is now accessible for proper documentation for the first time since the Antiquarian Society began work at this site. The Postmaster has received confirmation from the guild registrar — the clearance is logged as complete, and the Society's field record names your engagement as the decisive action that opened the vault.
